question: What is Global Arrays (GA)?
answer: Global Arrays (GA) is a Partitioned Global Address Space (PGAS) programming model that provides primitives for one-sided communication (Get, Put, Accumulate) and Atomic Operations (read increment). It supports blocking and non-blocking primitives and location consistency, with an I8 version available.
